I could compile it with this temporary solution : 

libcryptui by default checks if you have gnupg 2.0.*. Current version in gentoo is 2.1.15. 
So first we need to mask gnupg-2.1.15 
# nano /etc/portage/package.mask/gnupg 
Code:

=app-crypt/gnupg-2.1.15 

create local overlay for libcryptui 
# mkdir -p /usr/local/portage/metadata 
# mkdir /usr/local/portage/profiles 
# nano -w /usr/local/portage/metadata/layout.conf 
Code:

masters = gentoo my_repo 

# nano /usr/local/portage/profiles/repo_name 
Code:

my_repo 

Insert portdir_overlay in make.conf 
# nano /etc/portage/make.conf 
Code:

.. 
PORTDIR_OVERLAY="/usr/local/portage ${PORTDIR_OVERLAY}" 

Create local directories for overlay 
# mkdir -p /usr/local/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui 

Copy ebuild from portage tree to local overlay 
# cp /usr/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui/libcryptui-3.12.2.ebuild /usr/local/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui/ 

Go to overlay directory 
# cd /usr/local/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui/ 
Modify ebuild to comment patch 
You need to comment this line : "eapply "${FILESDIR}"/${PN}-3.12.2-gnupg-2.1.patch" 
# nano /usr/local/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui/libcryptui-3.12.2.ebuild 
Code:

.. 
src_prepare() { 
   # Support GnuPG 2.1, https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=745843[/color] 
        # eapply "${FILESDIR}"/${PN}-3.12.2-gnupg-2.1.patch 

   # FIXME: Do not mess with CFLAGS with USE="debug" 
   # sed -e '/CFLAGS="$CFLAGS -g -O0/d' \ 
      -e 's/-Werror//' \ 
      -i configure.ac configure || die "sed failed" 

   eautoreconf 
   gnome2_src_prepare 
} 
.. 

Generate a new manifest for ebuild 
# ebuild /usr/local/portage/x11-libs/libcryptui/libcryptui-3.1.12.ebuild manifest 

Now we can emerge libcryptui 
# emerge -vaq libcryptui 
Code:

[ebuild   R   ] x11-libs/libcryptui-3.12.2 [3.12.2] USE="introspection libnotify -debug" 

Would you like to merge these packages? [Yes/No] 
>>> Verifying ebuild manifests 
>>> Emerging (1 of 1) x11-libs/libcryptui-3.12.2::myrepo 
>>> Installing (1 of 1) x11-libs/libcryptui-3.12.2::myrepo 
>>> Recording x11-libs/libcryptui in "world" favorites file... 
>>> Jobs: 1 of 1 complete                           Load avg: 12.2, 10.8, 9.2 

